title: Holmlia SK
text:
Holmlia Sportsklubb is a <a href="Norway">Norwegian</a> sportsclub from the multi-cultural borough of <a href="Holmlia">Holmlia</a> in <a href="Oslo">Oslo</a>, with sections for <a href="association%20football">football</a>, <a href="team%20handball">handball</a>, <a href="floorball">floorball</a> and <a href="futsal">futsal</a>.
The men's football team plays in the <a href="4.%20divisjon">4. divisjon</a> from 2013, having last played in the <a href="3.%20divisjon">3. divisjon</a> in <a href="2012%20Norwegian%20Third%20Division">2012</a>. The club is also notable for developing talents, who are sold to the <a href="Norwegian%20top%20division">Norwegian top division</a> clubs such as <a href="V%C3%A5lerenga%20IF">Vålerenga</a> and <a href="Lillestr%C3%B8m%20SK">Lillestrøm</a>. Former players include <a href="Mohammed%20Fellah">Mohammed Fellah</a>, <a href="Mathis%20Bolly">Mathis Bolly</a>, <a href="Jonathan%20Parr">Jonathan Parr</a>, <a href="Akinsola%20Akinyemi">Akinsola Akinyemi</a>, <a href="Haitam%20Aleesami">Haitam Aleesami</a>, <a href="Ohi%20Omoijuanfo">Ohi Omoijuanfo</a>, <a href="Chuma%20Anene">Chuma Anene</a> and <a href="Adama%20Diomande">Adama Diomande</a>.
The club has won six Norwegian championship in floorball, five for women and one for men.
